Package: SiteAdapt
Type: Package
Title: Site Adaptation of Solar Irradiance Modeled Series
Version: 1.1.0
Author: Carlos M. Fernandez-Peruchena
Maintainer: Carlos M. Fernandez-Peruchena <cfernandez@cener.com>
Description: The SiteAdapt procedure improves the accuracy of modeled solar irradiance series
    through site-adaptation with coincident ground-based measurements relying on the use of a
    regression preprocessing followed by an empirical quantile mapping (eQM) correction.
    Fernandez-Peruchena et al (2020) <doi:10.3390/rs12132127>.
Imports: glmulti, solaR, hyfo, hydroGOF, RColorBrewer, ggplot2, ggpubr,
        stats
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
